Thank you for participating in this experiment.

The experiment will consist of one task with 200 trials.
The task will take around 10-15 minutes to complete. 

Press the spacebar to continue.

8.notes:
This template transmits the study data to a compatible server-side backend. Currently, it supports the PHP, Open Lab and JATOS backends.

It will wait until the data is transferred, showing a waiting screen with the text defined below, and continue with the remainder of the study after the transmission is complete. Please note that this screen will be skipped if no compatible backend is available.

content.text:
Congratulations!

You completed the experiment.
You can now close your browser.

If you think the top line is longer, press the "T" key.
If you think the bottom line is longer, press the "B" key.

In this kind of experiment, it is 
very important to have a controlled environment.

Therefore, we would like to ask you to perform this experiment 
in a quiet room without distractions. Please set this website to full screen 
mode and close all programs on your computer and tabs in your 
internet browser. Please also move your mouse 
cursor off the screen.

Please do not run any music in the background. However, we ask you 
to enable sound on your computer.

Next, we will provide some instructions regarding the task.

Press the spacebar to continue.
Here you see all line lengths at once.

Your task is to identify as fast and as accurately as possible
whether the top line or the bottom line is longer.
You will learn more about the different line lengths shortly.

For instance, in the scenario below the bottom line is longer. 
This means that the correct response in this trial would be "B".

Importantly, in each trial the line lengths and the
orientation of the arrows on both ends of the lines will change.

However, your task is to focus solely on the line lengths and to ignore 
the arrows. Perform the task as fast and as accurately as possible.

Press the spacebar to continue.

The aim of the first warm-up block is to familiarize you with
the task. For this reason, you will initially only see and judge 
whether the top line or the bottom line is longer without any arrows.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Place your fingers on the "T" and "B" letter on the keyboard,
then press the spacebar to begin the first warm-up block.

This was the first warm-up.

Press the spacebar to continue with the second warm-up block.

Place your fingers on the "T" and "B" letter on the keyboard,
then press the spacebar to begin the block.

content.text:
In this block, as in the real experiment, you will see the lines
with changing arrows on both ends. As explained earlier, your task is to judge 
whether the top line or the bottom line is longer.

Complete the task as fast and as accurately as possible.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Place your fingers on the "T" and "B" letter on the keyboard,
then press the spacebar to begin the second warm-up block.

This was the warm-up.

Press the spacebar to begin the real experiment.

We now start the real experiment. 

Remember: try to ignore the arrows and only judge the length
of the lines. In each trial, answer the question 'which line is longer?'.

Press the spacebar to continue.
